article.headline: Gardner-Webb 85, Ferrum 51
article.story: BOILING SPRINGS, N.C. -- Aaron Linn scored 17 points to lead Gardner-Webb to an 85-51 victory over Ferrum on Saturday. Auryn MacMillan finished with 16 points, 11 rebounds and six blocks for the Runnin' Bulldogs (4-7). Grayson Flittner and C.J. Hailey contributed 14 points apiece. Freshman Joshua Henley also grabbed a season-high 21 rebounds. The Panthers (6-4) were paced by Derek Mitchell, who finished with 16 points and 10 rebounds. Jerrell Wade had 15 and Keith Crump finished added 12. Gardner-Webb blocked 14 shots as a team, and limited Ferrum to 30 percent shooting (21-for-70). They also outrebounded the Panthers 53-33. On offense, the Runnin' Bulldogs shot 44.4 percent (28-for-63) and dished out 22 assists.
